<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100504989834546></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100504989834546><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=100504989834546>RE: A Rant</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=100504989834546#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 6th 7:31 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You're not the only person and shamans aren't the only classes cursed with a begger spell.&nbsp;&nbsp;Personally, when a shaman is in my group, I'm looking forward to the stat buffs, but I won't ask for them and sometimes I don't get them.  Still, Shamans are great buffers.  I know they get offensive spells but don't ask me anything about them.  I just assume that the person next to me knows how to play his character and doesn't need any pointers from me, unless I'm in need of a heal, and the healer isn't healing. ;(  Just play the game and stand by your convictions of what you think you should be.  There are 100 total jackasses for ever decent person and you usually have to deal with all 100 of the jerks before you find someone you like and trust.  But, hey, that's how the world is.  Norrath I'm talking about.<br>The only think you should ever worry about is wether YOU think you are doing the best that you can, be it buffing, healing, dotting, meleeing, and the all-important Role-playing.  Figure out what you are and how you use your vast abilities within the world.<br>Jerks aside, sometimes people ask for your magic for honorable reasons, not always just to benefit from shaman spells while not having to share xp or loot with one of you.<br>The answer to all your questions lay inbetween the extremes.  Good luck and hope you pursevere guy.<br>By the way, I play an sk, but have a druid, so I know how much having a beggar spell can suck.  Good thing about sk's, most spells are taps or self only buffs. hehe.  Still, I'm a knight first and always.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
