	   <tr><td colspan=2>Life as a grouping shaman can be hard untill peeps learn just we can do. First Learn EVERYTHING about your spells. You have to know what all your spells can do and what they "should" be used for. Next Make text macro's for the spells you use the most Including buff's! Why you may ask? So peeps know what your doing. With a wizzy or a cleric it is ez to see what they do, with us it is hard for some people to se it. Sure we buff'ed the tank +25 str and then +20 more with a short term battle buff but he killed it not us. Right? Let everyone know what you are doing. Text macro's can really help in this. Also ASK peeps "So how much did your str or AC go up with this buff?" Like you don't know =) But they might not. I have a Monk and a rouge I hunt with a lot and my buff's plus their skills ROCK. Read over you spells and think about them cast you short term combat buff's on the main tank EVERY pull it helps so much. Well Good luck and think about it.<br><br>Stoneblight 29th level Troll Shaman <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
